  "objective": [
    "N/A; This is a generic dungeon that can be used in random events in attempts to reward the PCs.\n"
  ],
  "description": [
    "An old forgotten wharf."
  ],
  "dm_guide": [
    "This wharf may once have been occupied by someone else, but currently is being used by a powerful wizard or sorcerer of sorts.\n",
    "They have potions scattered about, books, drawers, and a couple of statues.\n\n",
    "There are multiple ways to play this, but in essence: The area only becomes hostile once players start looting things.\n"
  ],
  "setting": "Small Dungeon Nearby Water",
  "tags": [
    "Random Encounter"
  ],
  "level_range": [
    3,
    10
  ],
  "resources": [],
  "maps": [
    {
      "name": "Forgotten Wharf",
      "url": "./maps/forgotten-wharf.jpg",
      "dm_guide": [
        "- The PCs can loot the house freely - they will get some potions from it, and leave.\n",
        "- Opening the chest on the ground floor next to the chair will trigger the two statues in the house, refer to NPCs\n",
        "- There is a 'secret' trapdoor inside the house under the bed, barely visible. This brings them to the basement through a ladder\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Basement",
      "url": "./maps/forgotten-wharf-basement.jpg",
      "dm_guide": [
        "- The basement does not have much interesting to loot on the main room, but once you go through the door several dangerous statues will trigger.\n",
        "- There's gold on the altar, free for the taking. The map might point to somewhere useful, or may just be a general map of the lands\n",
        "- Some sort of light is required, only the light from the trapdoor above gives off light\n"
      ]
    }
  ],
